385
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,000
Hello, Jack.

386
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,000
Ben.

387
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,000
Merry Christmas, Ben.

388
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,000
Jack Walton?

389
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,000
Young Jack Walton.

390
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,000
Spirits, what is?

391
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Well, have a good holiday, Jack.

392
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:04,000
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah, I remember him.

393
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,000
Both of them.

394
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:11,000
That's little Ben Benjamin and he used to...

395
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,000
See you next term, Jack.

396
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Next term.

397
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:20,000
Oh, yeah, they're off of the holidays and going home from school because it's Christmas time and all the children off home now.

398
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:24,000
And well, okay, well, no, not all the children there.

399
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,000
There was one.

