00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,000
Music?

513
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,000
And now your Christmas bullshit?

514
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,000
Yes, yes.

515
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:50,000
I've learned what you have to show me.

516
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Fezzowig, young Ebenezer, and Dick appear busily preparing for the party.

517
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,000
Oh, there.

518
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,000
Ebenezer, Dick, come on in.

519
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,000
Fezzowig?

520
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:02,000
It's old Fezzowig that I apprentice under.

521
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,000
Your master?

522
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,000
Oh, yes.

523
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,000
And the best that any boy could have.

524
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,000
And there's Dick Wilkins.

525
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:09,000
Oh, God.

526
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:12,000
He was very much attached to me, was Dick.

527
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,000
Oh, poor Dick.

528
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:16,000
My boys, my boys, no more work tonight.

529
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,000
Step away from your stations.

530
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,000
It's Christmas Eve.

531
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,000
Ebenezer, Dick, stop the work.

532
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,000
Let's have the shutters up before a man can say

533
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,000
Jack Robinson.

534
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,000
The music continues.

535
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,000
Chandeliers are pulled into position.

536
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:30,000
And Mistletoe, Holly, and Ivy are draped over everything

537
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:32,000
by buffling servants.

538
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:36,000
Dancers fill the stage for Fezzowig's wonderful Christmas party.

539
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:38,000
In the midst of the dancing and the laughter,

540
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:40,000
servants pass back and forth through the crowd

541
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:42,000
with huge platters of food.

542
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:44,000
At a pause in the music, young Ebenezer,

543
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,000
who was dancing, calls out.

544
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:50,000
Mr. Fezzowig, sir, you're a wonderful master.

545
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:53,000
A wonderful master.

546
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,000
A wonderful master.

547
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:01,000
The music changes suddenly, and the dancers

548
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,000
jerk into distorted postures

549
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:05,000
and then begin to move in slow motion.

550
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:07,000
The celebrants slowly exit,

551
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,000
performing a ghoulish dance to the jarring sounds.

552
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Well, that's fucking weird.

553
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:12,000
That was creepy.

554
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:15,000
Just because he gave us a party,

555
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:17,000
it was very small.

556
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,000
Small?

557
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:22,000
He spent a few pounds of your mortal money.

558
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:25,000
Three, four at the most.

559
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:29,000
Is that so much that he deserves this praise?

560
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,000
Yeah, okay, but listen.

561
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:32,000
It wasn't about the money.

562
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:34,000
He had the power to make us happy,

563
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:36,000
to make our service light,

564
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:38,000
or give us a shit-ton of work.

565
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,000
The happiness he gives us

566
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:43,000
quite as great as if it had cost a fortune.

567
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:47,000
That's what a good master is.

568
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,000
Yes?

569
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:52,000
Uh, nothing.

570
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:55,000
Something, I think.

571
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:58,000
Well, I should like to be able to say

572
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:00,000
