573
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,000
That's all.

574
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,000
But this is all in your past.

575
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:06,000
Your clerk, Cratchit, couldn't be here.

576
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:08,000
No, no, no, no, of course not.

577
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:10,000
It was an idle thought.

578
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,000
Are we done?

579
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,000
Motioning for the waltz music to begin.

580
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:15,000
Nearly.

581
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:18,000
Hearing the waltz and remembering it.

582
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:21,000
Oh, surely it's enough.

583
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:23,000
Haven't you tormented me enough?

584
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:25,000
Young Ebenezer has seen waltzing

585
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:27,000
with his sweetheart.

586
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:29,000
I only show the past,

587
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:31,000
what it promised you.

588
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:34,000
Look, another promise.

589
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:37,000
Oh, oh, yes.

590
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:39,000
I'd forgotten her.

591
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:41,000
Don't they dance beautifully?

592
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:44,000
So young, so young.

593
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:47,000
I would have married her if only...

594
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:50,000
Can you love me, sweet Ebenezer,

595
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,000
a simple janitor?

596
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:54,000
I bring no dowry into my marriage,

597
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,000
only me, only love.

598
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:59,000
It is no currency that you can buy and sell with,

599
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:01,000
but we can live with it.

600
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,000
Can you?

601
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,000
She pauses, then returns the ring

602
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,000
Scrooge gave her as his pledge.

603
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,000
I release you, sweet Ebenezer,

604
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:12,000
for the love of the man you once were.

605
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,000
Will that man win me again

606
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,000
now that he is free?

607
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:18,000
If only it held me to it.

608
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:20,000
You shouldn't have let me go.

609
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:22,000
I was young, I did love you.

610
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:24,000
We have never lied to one another.

611
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:27,000
May you be happy in the life you have chosen.

612
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,000
Goodbye!

613
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:29,000
She runs out.

614
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:31,000
Young Ebenezer slowly leaves.

615
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:36,000
No, no, it didn't go down like that.

616
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,000
You cannot change now,

617
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:42,000
what you would not change then.

618
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:45,000
I am your mistakes, Ebenezer Scrooge.

619
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:49,000
All of the things you could have done and did not.

620
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,000
Then go.

621
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,000
I've done with them.

622
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,000
I'll live with them.

623
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:55,000
I've been living with them,

624
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:57,000
and I'll continue to live with them.

625
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:59,000
There is another Christmas,

626
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,000
seven years ago,

627
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,000
when Marley died.

628
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,000
No.

629
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:06,000
I will not see it.

630
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,000
I will not.

631
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,000
He dies.

632
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:09,000
I couldn't prevent it.

633
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,000
I couldn't stop it.

634
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:13,000
I didn't choose for him to die on Christmas Day, okay?

635
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:16,000
And when his day was chosen,

636
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:18,000
what did you do then?

637
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:21,000
Well, I looked after his affairs.

638
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,000
His business.

639
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:25,000
Yes, his business.

640
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:26,000
Mine.

641
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:28,000
It was all I had.

642
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,000
All I could do in this world.

643
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:33,000
I have nothing to do with the world that comes after.

644
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:36,000
Then I will leave you.

645
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,000
Hold up.

646
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:38,000
Not yet.

647
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,000
No, you can't leave me here.

648
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:41,000
You gotta tell me what I have to do.

649
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,000
What's going on with the other spirits?

650
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,000
They will come.

651
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,000
Bond you?

652
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:46,000
What are you gonna do?

653
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:49,000
I am always with you.

654
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,000
Oh, that's creepy.

655
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,000
Scrooge numbly heads to bed.

656
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:55,000
Signal the chiming of Scrooge's bell.

657
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:58,000
Scrooge sits upright in bed as he hears the chimes.

658
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,000
One minute until when?

659
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:03,000
No one here?

660
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,000
Well, no one's coming.

661
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,000
A larger clock strikes one o'clock.

662
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,000
A light comes on.

663
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:28,000
Scrooge becomes aware of it and goes slowly to it.

664
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:31,000
He sees the second spirit, the spirit of Christmas present,

665
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:33,000
who looks like Fezzowick.

666
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:35,000
Fezzowick?

667
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:37,000
Hello, Scrooge.

668
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,000
But you can't be.

669
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:41,000
Not Fezzowick.

670
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:43,000
Is that who you see me as?

671
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,000
Yeah.

672
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:48,000
Well, do you hear me as him as well?

673
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,000
Uh-huh, yeah.

674
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:52,000
Well, you should probably get your eyes and ears checked, old man,

675
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,000
because I am not that gentleman.

676
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:56,000
So I'm sorry to disappoint you.

677
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,000
But you're not...

678
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,000
No, no I'm not, Scrooge.

679
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:03,000
You have never seen the like of me before.

680
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:06,000
I am the ghost of Christmas present,

681
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:07,000
here to give you...

682
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,000
Hold on.

683
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:12,000
You still choose to see what you will, don't you, Scrooge?

684
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,000
But you're not going to see it anymore.

685
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:18,000
Not if you take a walk with me on this Christmas Eve.

686
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,000
Would you take a walk with me?

687
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,000
Yeah, I'm in my...

688
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,000
I'm in my jammies.

689
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:26,000
Oh, don't worry about that.

690
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,000
Take my tails, dear boy,

691
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:30,000
for we're heading out into the world.

692
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:33,000
Like the edges of your pants?

693
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:35,000
No, my tail.

694
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,000
I am a spirit with a tail.

695
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:39,000
That's what I wanted when I took the role, so...

696
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:40,000
Just grab the tail.

697
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,000
It's totally fine.

698
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,000
Oh, okay.

699
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:43,000
Don't wag it.

700
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:44,000
It's weird.

701
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,000
Wait, wait, hold on.

702
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,000
You're wagging it.

703
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:47,000
Just...

704
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:48,000
Okay, let's go.

705
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,000
What is it now?

706
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,000
Wait.

707
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:52,000
Christmas present, you said?

708
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,000
That I did.

709
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:55,000
Then we're traveling here?

710
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:56,000
Yes.

711
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,000
In this town?

712
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:58,000
Yeah.

713
00:32:58,000 --> 00:32:59,000
Yeah, of course.

714
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:01,000
Okay, then we could walk, right?

715
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:03,000
Because you fly in, well, it's...

716
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:05,000
It's too much for an old man's hut.

717
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:07,000
The first one didn't talk about...

718
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,000
They definitely did.

719
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,000
I know them fairly well.

720
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:11,000
So it's your Christmas, Scoot.

721
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:12,000
Scooch.

722
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:14,000
That's what they used to call me when I was a kid.

723
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,000
And it's really offensive, and I don't like it.

724
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,000
I apologize.

725
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:19,000
I apologize, Scooch.

726
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,000
Scrooge.

727
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:22,000
It's your Christmas.

728
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:24,000
I am merely the guide.

729
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,000
Can we whack?

730
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:27,000
Fine.

731
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,000
The spirit nods.

732
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,000
Ugh.

733
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:30,000
Okay, well, we a guide meet you.

734
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,000
Oh, you're gonna like this one.

735
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:32,000
Are you ready?

736
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,000
You ready?

737
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,000
No.

738
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:35,000
I've been ready this whole time.

739
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:36,000
Well, get ready.

740
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,000
It's Bob Cratchit's.

741
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:38,000
Let's go.

742
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:39,000
My clerk?

743
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:40,000
Yeah, you said you wanted to talk to him.

744
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,000
That's...

745
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,000
That's what Christmas Past told me.

746
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:47,000
Don't worry if you don't want to talk to Bob.

747
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,000
You won't have to.

748
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:50,000
In fact, it may be better that way.

749
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:52,000
Yeah, well, you know, it shouldn't be too much of a trip.

750
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:55,000
With 15 Bob a week, how far off can it be?

751
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:57,000
It's a world away, Scrooge.

752
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:00,000
At least that far.

753
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,000
Scrooge and the spirit start to step off a curb

754
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:05,000
when a funeral procession enters with the child's coffin,

755
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:08,000
followed by the poor house children who are singing.

756
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:12,000
Follow them, Scrooge.

757
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:16,000
Follow the music.

758
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:19,000
The procession follows the coffin off stage.

759
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:22,000
Scrooge and the spirit exit after the procession.

760
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:26,000
As they leave, the lights focus on Mrs. Cratchit and her children.

761
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:30,000
Mrs. Cratchit sings as she puts Tiny Tim and the other children to bed,

762
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,000
all in one bed.

763
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:34,000
She pulls a dark blanket over them.

764
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:42,000
When you wake, you shall have all the pretty little horses,

765
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:53,000
demon steeds, poison breath freed, all the pretty demon horses.

766
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:57,000
Go to sleep now, all of you.

767
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:01,000
Tomorrow is Christmas.

768
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:05,000
She kisses them and goes to Bob Cratchit, who is by the hearth.

769
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:08,000
How did Tiny Tim behave?

770
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:10,000
Oh, as good as can be expected.

771
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:12,000
And better.

772
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:15,000
You know, he told me it was super cute coming home,

773
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:18,000
that he hoped people might see him in the church

774
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,000
because he's differently abled

775
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:27,000
and they might be able to reflect on how good they have it.

776
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:31,000
That's kind of fucked up.

777
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:34,000
But he's a good boy.

778
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:37,000
The second spirit and Scrooge enter.

779
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:40,000
Mrs. Cratchit feels a sudden draft.

780
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:41,000
Oh.

781
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,000
The wind.

782
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:44,000
Hurry.

783
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:46,000
She gets up and shuts the door.

784
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:47,000
Hurry along, Scrooge.

785
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,000
Quick.

786
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:51,000
Like the wind here.

787
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:54,000
