I think that little bell he's always ringing at me

1053
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:24,000
is silver enough to sell.

1054
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:26,000
The three of them move toward the nightstand,

1055
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:28,000
and Scrooge cries out.

1056
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:30,000
No more! No more!

1057
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:32,000
As the spirit directs Scrooge's attention

1058
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:34,000
to the tableau of the three thieves

1059
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:36,000
standing poised over the silver bell,

1060
00:46:36,000 --> 00:46:38,000
Scrooge bursts out of the house,

1061
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:40,000
clad only in his knight shirt.

1062
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:43,000
Listen, I know I'm half naked, but I cannot.

1063
00:46:43,000 --> 00:46:44,000
I can't.

1064
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:47,000
This room, it's too, like a cheerless place

1065
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:50,000
and it's like so familiar and I won't see it.

1066
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,000
Let's go. Let's go anywhere but here.

1067
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:54,000
I mean, you decorated it, but yeah, sure.

1068
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:56,000
Let's look at house number two.

1069
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:57,000
Come on down.

1070
00:46:57,000 --> 00:47:00,000
The spirit directs his attention to the Cratchit house.

1071
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:03,000
The children are sitting together near Ms. Cratchit,

1072
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:05,000
who is sewing a coat.

1073
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:07,000
Peter reads by the light of the coals.

1074
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:10,000
And he took a child and sat him in the midst of them,

1075
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:12,000
putting her hand to her face.

1076
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:15,000
The light tires my eyes so.

1077
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:16,000
Pause.

1078
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:18,000
They're better now.

1079
00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:22,000
It makes them tired to try to see by firelight.

1080
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:26,000
And I would not show reddened eyes to your father

1081
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:29,000
when he comes home from the world.

1082
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:32,000
It must be near his time now.

1083
00:47:32,000 --> 00:47:34,000
Pasty to think.

1084
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:37,000
But he walks slower than he used to

1085
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:41,000
these last few days, mother.

1086
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:44,000
I have known him to walk with tiny Tim

1087
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:48,000
upon his shoulder very fast indeed.

1088
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:51,000
She catches herself, then hurries on.

1089
00:47:51,000 --> 00:47:54,000
But he was very light to carry,

1090
00:47:54,000 --> 00:47:56,000
and his father loved him,

1091
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:58,000
so that was no trouble.

1092
00:47:58,000 --> 00:48:00,000
No trouble.

1093
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:03,000
She hears Bob Cratchit approaching.

1094
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:05,000
Smiles, everyone.

1095
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:07,000
Smiles.

1096
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:09,000
Entering.

1097
00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:12,000
My dear, Peter.

1098
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:14,000
All the other children.

1099
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:15,000
How's it coming?

1100
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:16,000
Handing him the coat.

1101
00:48:16,000 --> 00:48:18,000
Nearly done.

1102
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:20,000
Yes, yes, good, good, good.

1103
00:48:20,000 --> 00:48:23,000
I'm sure that it will be done long before Sunday.

1104
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:25,000
Sunday.

1105
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:28,000
You went today, then, Robert.

1106
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:31,000
Yes, it's already.

1107
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:35,000
Two o'clock and a nice place.

1108
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:38,000
It would have done you good to see how green it is.

1109
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:39,000
But you'll see it often.

1110
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:41,000
I promised him that.

1111
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:44,000
That I would walk there on Sunday often.

1112
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:47,000
We mustn't hurt ourselves for it, Robert.

1113
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:50,000
No, no, he wouldn't have wanted that.

1114
00:48:50,000 --> 00:48:51,000
But come now.

1115
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:53,000
You won't guess who I've seen.

1116
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:55,000
Scrooge's nephew, Fred.

1117
00:48:55,000 --> 00:48:57,000
And he asked after us,

1118
00:48:57,000 --> 00:48:59,000
and he said he was heartily sorry,

1119
00:48:59,000 --> 00:49:02,000
and to give his respect to my good wife.

1120
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:05,000
How he ever knew that, I don't know.

1121
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:07,000
Knew what, my dear?

1122
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:09,000
Why, that you were a good wife.

1123
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:10,000
Everybody knows that.

1124
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:12,000
Well, I hope that they do.

1125
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:15,000
Heartily sorry, he said, for your good wife.

1126
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:18,000
And if I can be of service to you in any way,

1127
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:20,000
then he gave me his card.

1128
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:21,000
That's where I live.

1129
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:24,000
And Peter, I shouldn't be at all surprised

1130
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:26,000
if he got you a position.

1131
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:28,000
Only hear that, Peter.

1132
00:49:28,000 --> 00:49:30,000
And then you'll be keeping company

1133
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:32,000
with some young girl and setting up for yourself.

1134
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:33,000
Aw, come on.

1135
00:49:33,000 --> 00:49:36,000
Well, it will happen one day.

1136
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:39,000
But remember, when that day comes, as it must,

1137
00:49:39,000 --> 00:49:42,000
we must none of us forget poor Tiny Tim

1138
00:49:42,000 --> 00:49:45,000
and this first parting in our family.

1139
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:47,000
He died?

1140
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:49,000
No.

1141
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:51,000
No.

1142
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:54,000
He steps back, and the scene disappears.

1143
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:56,000
He moves away from the spirit.

1144
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:04,000
Because he wouldn't.

1145
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:07,000
No, you can't tell me that he died.

1146
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:10,000
For that Christmas hasn't happened yet.

1147
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:12,000
And I will let it happen.

1148
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:14,000
I'll be there.

1149
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:15,000
Yeah, me.

1150
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:17,000
And yeah, I knew it.

1151
00:50:17,000 --> 00:50:19,000
And I couldn't look.

1152
00:50:19,000 --> 00:50:21,000
And I won't be able to help.

1153
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:22,000
I won't.

1154
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:26,000
But spirit, hear me.

1155
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:28,000
I'm not the man I was.

1156
00:50:28,000 --> 00:50:32,000
I won't be that man that I've been all these years.

1157
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:36,000
So why show me all this if I'm past all hope?

1158
00:50:36,000 --> 00:50:40,000
Assure me that yet I may change these shadows that you show me?

1159
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:42,000
Let the boy live.

1160
00:50:42,000 --> 00:50:44,000
I'll honor Christmas in my heart

1161
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:47,000
and try to keep it there all the other days of the year.

1162
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:51,000
And I will in past, the present, and the future.

1163
00:50:51,000 --> 00:50:55,000
The spirits of all three is going to live within me.

1164
00:50:55,000 --> 00:50:58,000
But not in a weird way, but like in my heart and stuff.

1165
00:50:58,000 --> 00:51:01,000
And I won't shadow the lessons that I was taught today.

1166
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:03,000
Just tell me that I'm not too late.

1167
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:08,000
Blackout!

1168
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:13,000
When the lights come up again, Scrooge is in bed.

1169
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:15,000
The third spirit has disappeared.

1170
00:51:15,000 --> 00:51:18,000
Scrooge awakens and looks around his room.

1171
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:20,000
The curtains.

1172
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:22,000
They're mine and they're real.

1173
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:23,000
And they're not sold.

1174
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:24,000
They're here.

1175
00:51:24,000 --> 00:51:25,000
And I'm here.

1176
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:28,000
And I have to give a raise to my house help.

1177
00:51:28,000 --> 00:51:31,000
Because otherwise when I die, they're going to rob me blind.

1178
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:33,000
And I don't blame them.

1179
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:34,000
And I'm here.

1180
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:36,000
The shadows has been dispelled.

1181
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:38,000
And they will be.

1182
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:39,000
I know they will be.

1183
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:41,000
He dresses himself hurriedly.

1184
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:43,000
I can't go out naked.

1185
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:45,000
That's a modesty law we have here.

1186
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:47,000
Now I don't know what to do.

1187
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:50,000
As light as a feather, I have a second life.

1188
00:51:50,000 --> 00:51:52,000
I'm merry as a boy again.

1189
00:51:52,000 --> 00:51:53,000
Merry Christmas.

1190
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:55,000
Merry Christmas.

1191
00:51:55,000 --> 00:51:57,000
I've got to practice.

1192
00:51:57,000 --> 00:51:58,000
Happy New Year to all the world.

1193
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:01,000
I don't think I've said those words in my entire life.

1194
00:52:01,000 --> 00:52:02,000
Hello there.

1195
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:03,000
Whoop.

1196
00:52:03,000 --> 00:52:05,000
I've never whooped before.

1197
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:06,000
Hello.

1198
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:07,000
What day of the month is it?

1199
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:08,000
That's a weird question to ask.

1200
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:11,000
But I'm wondering how long did the spirits keep me?

1201
00:52:11,000 --> 00:52:12,000
Whatever.

1202
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:13,000
I don't care.

1203
00:52:13,000 --> 00:52:15,000
He opens the window and calls to a boy on the street below.

1204
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:16,000
You there, boy.

1205
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:18,000
What's today?

1206
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:20,000
Eh?

1207
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:24,000
Like the day, my fine fellow.

1208
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:26,000
Today?

1209
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:29,000
Why, it's Christmas Day.

1210
00:52:29,000 --> 00:52:31,000
I thought I was the dense one here.

1211
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:32,000
It's Christmas Day?

1212
00:52:32,000 --> 00:52:34,000
I haven't missed it.

1213
00:52:34,000 --> 00:52:36,000
The spirits have done it all in one night.

1214
00:52:36,000 --> 00:52:38,000
Gosh, they can do anything, hey?

1215
00:52:38,000 --> 00:52:40,000
Okay, so of course they can.

1216
00:52:40,000 --> 00:52:42,000
Of course they can save Tim.

1217
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:43,000
Excuse me.

1218
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,000
Hello.

1219
00:52:44,000 --> 00:52:45,000
Yes, my fine fellow.

1220
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:47,000
Hello?

1221
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:52,000
Do you know the Chickaneers in the next street in the corner?

1222
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:55,000
I should hope I do.

1223
00:52:55,000 --> 00:52:57,000
Oh, you're so smart.

1224
00:52:57,000 --> 00:52:59,000
Oh, a remarkable boy.

1225
00:52:59,000 --> 00:53:03,000
Okay, so do you know whether they sold that prize turkey that was hanging up there?

1226
00:53:03,000 --> 00:53:04,000
Not the small little one.

1227
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:05,000
That thing was bullshit.

1228
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:07,000
But like the really big one.

1229
00:53:07,000 --> 00:53:10,000
The one as big as me?

1230
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:12,000
Yes, what a delightful boy.

1231
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:13,000
Yes, my bucko.

1232
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:14,000
Yeah, I'm a bucko.

1233
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:16,000
Yeah, you are.

1234
00:53:16,000 --> 00:53:17,000
It's in there now.

1235
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:19,000
It's hanging in there.

1236
00:53:19,000 --> 00:53:20,000
It is?

1237
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:22,000
Go and buy it.

1238
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:23,000
I don't have any money.

1239
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:24,000
No, no, for realsies.

1240
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:25,000
Go and buy it.

1241
00:53:25,000 --> 00:53:28,000
And tell him to bring it here.

1242
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:30,000
And I'll pay him when they get here.

1243
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:31,000
Don't you worry about it.

1244
00:53:31,000 --> 00:53:32,000
They know I'm good for it.

1245
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:35,000
And I'm going to give them the direction where to take it.

1246
00:53:35,000 --> 00:53:36,000
Okay?

1247
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:39,000
So you come back with the butcher and the really big turkey.

1248
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:40,000
And I'll give you a shelling.

1249
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:44,000
Or if you come back in less than two minutes, I'll give you half a crown.

1250
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:46,000
You betcha.

1251
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:48,000
He exits.

1252
00:53:48,000 --> 00:53:51,000
I'll send it to Bob Cratchits.

1253
00:53:51,000 --> 00:53:53,000
He's not going to know who sent it.

1254
00:53:53,000 --> 00:53:55,000
Oh, it's going to be twice the size of Tiny Tim.

1255
00:53:55,000 --> 00:53:57,000
It really needs to make sure it doesn't fall on him.

1256
00:53:57,000 --> 00:53:59,000
That would be a really dark twist in this story.

1257
00:53:59,000 --> 00:54:02,000
But, like, what a Christmas dinner it'll make.

1258
00:54:02,000 --> 00:54:04,000
Carolers suddenly appear, singing,

1259
00:54:04,000 --> 00:54:10,000
Hark the herald angels sing.

1260
00:54:10,000 --> 00:54:14,000
Scrooge leans out the window and joins them in the song.

1261
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:19,000
Glory to the newborn king.

1262
00:54:19,000 --> 00:54:20,000
Oh, wow.

1263
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:22,000
Oh, God, I'm not dressed.

1264
00:54:22,000 --> 00:54:23,000
I got to dress.

1265
00:54:23,000 --> 00:54:24,000
I got to dress.

1266
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:25,000
Christmas day.

1267
00:54:25,000 --> 00:54:26,000
I got to look my best.

1268
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:28,000
I got to look my best for such a day.

1269
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:30,000
Where's my silk shirt?

1270
00:54:30,000 --> 00:54:32,000
The boy and the butcher run in with the turkey.

1271
00:54:32,000 --> 00:54:35,000
Oh, God, I'm not dressed.

1272
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:36,000
What?

1273
00:54:36,000 --> 00:54:37,000
You're back already?

1274
00:54:37,000 --> 00:54:39,000
Whoa, that's a turkey.

1275
00:54:39,000 --> 00:54:42,000
You can't carry that all the way back to the Cratchits.

1276
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:43,000
Okay, here, boy.

1277
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:45,000
Here's your half a crown.

1278
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:47,000
And here's an address in Camden Town.

1279
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:48,000
You see that?

1280
00:54:48,000 --> 00:54:49,000
See that?

1281
00:54:49,000 --> 00:54:50,000
It gets there.

1282
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:52,000
Here, money for the cap and for the turkey.

1283
00:54:52,000 --> 00:54:53,000
And for you, good man.

1284
00:54:53,000 --> 00:54:56,000
The boy and the butcher, delighted, catch the money and run out.

1285
00:54:56,000 --> 00:55:00,000
Scrooge sees the gentleman visitors walking by the window.

1286
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:02,000
Hello there.

1287
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:04,000
Oh, oh, hi.

1288
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:07,000
My dear, my dear, how do you do?

1289
00:55:07,000 --> 00:55:09,000
I hope you succeeded yesterday.

1290
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:11,000
It was very kind of you to stop by and see me.

1291
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:13,000
Mr. Scrooge?

1292
00:55:13,000 --> 00:55:14,000
That's my name.

1293
00:55:14,000 --> 00:55:15,000
Don't wear it out.

1294
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:18,000
Although that's probably not like a really good name for you to hear

1295
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:21,000
because associations and whatnot.

1296
00:55:21,000 --> 00:55:24,000
But allow me to ask for your forgiveness.

1297
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:27,000
And will you have the goodness to add this?

1298
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:29,000
Throwing him a purse?

1299
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:31,000
To your good work.

1300
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:33,000
Oh, oh, my goodness.

1301
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:35,000
My dear Mr. Scrooge, are you serious?

1302
00:55:35,000 --> 00:55:36,000
If you please.

1303
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:37,000
And not a penny less.

1304
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:41,000
A great many back payments are included in it, I assure you.

1305
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:43,000
Will you do me that favor?

1306
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:46,000
My dear sir, we don't know what we can say to such generosity.

1307
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:49,000
Say nothing, just accept it.

1308
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:50,000
Come and see me.

1309
00:55:50,000 --> 00:55:51,000
Will you come and see me?

1310
00:55:51,000 --> 00:55:53,000
Yeah, of course we will.

1311
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:54,000
Thank you.

1312
00:55:54,000 --> 00:55:55,000
I'm much obliged to you.

1313
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,000
Thank you 50 times.

1314
00:55:57,000 --> 00:55:59,000
And God's bless you.

1315
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:01,000
And Merry Christmas.

1316
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:02,000
Merry Christmas to you, sir.

1317
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:04,000
Merry Christmas.

1318
00:56:04,000 --> 00:56:08,000
Running downstairs out of his house and on to the street.

